Update #13
Display Configuration Procedure for shell only
user avatar
Argon FortyCreator
February 2, 2026

To set the resolution to 1920x1200 @ 60Hz, follow these steps to edit the cmdline.txt file:

The cmdline.txt file contains the boot parameters for the kernel.

1. Open a terminal and edit the cmdline.txt file with administrative privileges:

sudo nano /boot/firmware/cmdline.txt

2. Add the following parameter at the end of the existing line (do not create a new line; everything in this file must stay on a single line):

video=HDMI-A-2:1920x1200@60e

3. Press Ctrl+O, then Enter,  Ctrl+X to save the changes and exit the editor.

4. Reboot your Raspberry Pi for the new settings to take effect:

reboot

5. How to verify after boot

Run:

xrandr

or

cat /sys/class/drm/card*-HDMI-A-2/modes
